FBIS4-59251 "drnes092dd_94009" FBIS-NES-94-092 Daily Report 11 May 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Palestinian Affairs 'Arafat, Castro Hold Talks in Pretoria 'Arafat, Castro Hold Talks in Pretoria LD1105183694 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 11 May 94 LD1105183694 Algiers Voice of Palestine Arabic BFN [Text] President Yasir 'Arafat met the Cuban president, comrade Fidel Castro, in Pretoria yesterday evening. During the meeting, recent developments with regard to the Palestinian cause were discussed. President 'Arafat gave a detailed explanation of the developments in the peace process. President Castro expressed his full support for the great efforts made by President 'Arafat and his brothers at the PLO Executive Committee to recover the Palestinian people's rights under these conditions. He stressed that peace, like war, required courage, pointing out that the Palestinian people's great sacrifices have been crowned with this victory, which is the way to full independence. The meeting was attended by the members of the delegation accompanying President 'Arafat and by the Cuban foreign minister.
